1 Overview
Outlined in this document is the set of intended topics, objectives and takeaways
from a prospective ‘ways of working workshop’ hosted for the CT programme
April 23rd 2026. At a high level, such an event will look to provide key answers
to set the direction of travel for three primary aspects of the developer experience:
environment management, test automation strategy, and fast routes to
production.
Delivery of the event would be conducted on a small-scale, including only
members of the D365, DevOps, Release Management and Test teams. Inclusion
of stakeholders from the VOA or NGR projects will be at the discretion
of Cognizant leadership. Subject to appropriate space, the workshop would run
similarly to the ‘problem solving days’ hosted by Alan O’Mahoney, with four
tables with pre-prepared discussion points with attendees assigned to the most
relevant group to their roles.
A successful event would deliver a set of programme objectives to propose
to the client for R1.11. Following the session, a business case including financial
estimates would be commissioned for completion across PI-5 whilst preparation
for each of the key takeaways takes place. Any blockers to achieving the
ideal ways of working should be flagged and listed at the April workshop, and
presented to the VOA Assurance lead to seek routes for resolution.
